  "texts": [
    "Curtains, blinds, and other methods for covering windows may not provide sufficient control over the illumination of the room.",
    "Instead, we think that a well thought out setup for an eye tracking lab uses indirect light, ideally provided by some movable lamps that are aimed at the walls or ceilings.",
    "If conversely, recordings are made in outdoor conditions, special measures such as visors blocking infrared light (e.g., Matthis et al., 2018) may be used to reduce data loss and improve recording quality.",
    "This and other considerations regarding working with uncontrolled lighting conditions during wearable eye tracking recordings are discussed in Fu et al. (2024).",
    "Lastly, depending on one's needs, one may wish to consider the color of walls and tables in the lab."
  ],
